<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="LE4" checkit-title="Linear Systems with Infinitely-Many Solutions">
  <statement>
    <p>
Consider the following
system of linear equations.
      <me>
        \begin{matrix}
 -4 \, x_{1} &amp;  +  &amp; 8 \, x_{2} &amp;  -  &amp; x_{3} &amp; = &amp; 9 \\
 5 \, x_{1} &amp;  -  &amp; 10 \, x_{2} &amp;  +  &amp; x_{3} &amp; = &amp; -12 \\
 -4 \, x_{1} &amp;  +  &amp; 8 \, x_{2} &amp;  +  &amp; 2 \, x_{3} &amp; = &amp; 18 \\
 2 \, x_{1} &amp;  -  &amp; 4 \, x_{2} &amp;  +  &amp; 4 \, x_{3} &amp; = &amp; 6 \\
 \end{matrix}
        
      </me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to find a simpler system or vector equation
that has the same solution set.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to describe this solution set using set notation.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>

  <answer>
    <p>
      <me>\mathrm{RREF}\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
-4 &amp; 8 &amp; -1 &amp; 9 \\
5 &amp; -10 &amp; 1 &amp; -12 \\
-4 &amp; 8 &amp; 2 &amp; 18 \\
2 &amp; -4 &amp; 4 &amp; 6
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; -2 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me>
      The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \, a - 3 \\
a \\
3
\end{array}\right] \,\middle|\, a \in\mathbb R \right\} </m>.
    </p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
